inn_save_lef_ignore_abstracts(25.10)      inn_save_lef_ignore_abstracts(25.10)

Name
       inn_save_lef_ignore_abstracts

Syntax
       inn_save_lef_ignore_abstracts {True | False}

       Type: Boolean

       Default: False

       Specifies  whether to remember a list of unused LEF block macros (CLASS
       BLOCK or RING) so they are not read back with  restoreDesign.   If  you
       have  a large number of LEF blocks (for example, memories) that are not
       used in this design, this can speedup restoreDesign and  reduce  memory
       by  skipping  those  LEF cells. Small blocks with less then 10 pins are
       still read in, because they are sometimes added later in the flow.

Related Information
              * restoreDesign

